This past Sunday was the second public event for @seenlibrary, a project by @jordanrisa to create a community with a shared love of books and also to host book drives to provide reading material to different nonprofits like the Claremont Forum’s Prison Library Project. 

I’ve been wanting to attend one for a long time, and I was really excited for this one at @tea__at__shiloh. I met a lot of great people in such a beautiful space and got to talk about books which is always a treat for me. I already can’t wait till the next one 📚

It’s not even February anymore but I’ve been meaning to post vday things for the longest. We spent it at the Hammer at the Didion exhibition with the kids and then got Roscoes🧇💌. Sooo here’s some (second half of) February things instead, including the crazy snow we got to experience in our front yard.

“I like to feel his eyes on me when I look away.” 

I tried a custom temporary tattoo thing last month and based the design off of my favorite movie trilogy, the Before Trilogy (this listening booth scene and the phone call scene kill me) by Richard Linklater whose work I love so much. There’s a sunset, sunrise, and midnight all in one (inspired by a TikTok design!). Swipe to see! It’s almost faded, and I’m not sure what I think about it yet because I’m (a Libra and) so indecisive. I’ve always entertained the idea of a tattoo but can never commit to anything 🤷🏻‍♀️ What are some fun tattoo ideas you have? I always thought I would do a literary quote or something, but again, I don’t know which I would stick with and also where I’d put it and not get sick of it.
#beforesunrise #beforetrilogy

On Motherhood: Melissa and Johanna 👯‍♀️: For the launch of new colors in our Mommy and Me collection, we’re celebrating motherhood.

Since motherhood is a unique journey for every mama, we’re listening to diverse stories from our community. We got to chat with @melissasonico, a college English professor, freelance writer, jewelry designer, and content creator about the perspective kids can provide, what they can teach you, and making time for creativity. 

Link in bio to read the full interview with Melissa. ✔️#BeyondYogaJournal

Just in time for back to school, both Johanna and Harrison got their annual eye exams from @warbyparker. It’s super important for us to make sure their eyes stay healthy and keep their prescriptions up to date. The staff at Warby Parker were so helpful and made sure the kids were comfortable and had fun during their exams.

Harrison used to need glasses, but his eyes have gotten stronger since, and he doesn’t need to wear them for now. (The filmy glasses were to help his eyes adjust after getting them dilated during the exam.) Jojo got her first prescription and we’re waiting on her new glasses. She’s excited to wear them to school—she just started TK this month, and loves it already. The frames she chose are the Jane in Amethyst Crystal from the Warby Jr. line! Let me know if you have any questions in the meantime.

Pretty much all of my frames are from @warbyparker as well! 🤓 #sponsored #warbyparker

Some of my favorites for everyday and for last-minute gifting—you can also get your loved ones gift cards to any of these shops in time for Christmas:

💝 Everything from @noto_botanics. Clean beauty, inclusive, all-around amazing and great smelling skincare. Use my code for 15% off MELISSA15
💝 I’m (a lot of the time) wary when it comes to supplements and all, but @moonjuice consistently comes through. My favorites are the Magnesi-OM for sleep and gut health and Ting for some energy and metabolic support, and these comfy socks!
💝 and you all know there’s something from @madewell in my ootd at all times, basically. Right now I’m loving the essential bucket tote and a thin silver chain necklace
💝 Get pies from @ilikepiebakeshop if you’re local to the LA area!
💝 Books are an easy gifting go-to, especially giving someone books you love that remind you of the person receiving it. 
💝 @ozma_of_california is Filipina-designed and made in Southern California. I live in this brand as well. Use code SONICO25 for 25% off which is rare 
💝 I go through bottles of @oseamalibu undaria argan oil, ocean eyes, and their hyaluronic serum. Definitely worth it. 
💝 @baggu is another easy gifting solution. Everyone needs and loves reusable totes and baggu has the best, including other items like my @sandyliang bow bag collab
